title: Hayne’s mark of respect from Packers
text:
Jarryd Hayne gets mark of respect from Green Bay Packers, 49ers under fire - US View Staff writers FOX SPORTS Jarryd Hayne gets mark of respect from Green Bay Packers, 49ers under fire - US View Staff writers FOX SPORTS Jarryd Hayne told 'you should be slaying' 1:22 
NFL: Chatting to 'The Game' host Damon Bruce on US radio station 95.7 San Francisco 49ers punt returner Jarryd Hayne admits his Australian accent does win him extra female attention October 3rd 2015 3 days ago /video/video.news.com.au/Sport/More Sports/ 
JARRYD Hayne is looking at home as an NFL punt returner and is posting numbers that stack up well against rivals - though his special teams unit is struggling. 
That’s the verdict from US media after the Australian 49ers ace had a limited role in a home loss to Green Bay. Hayne made a couple of returns for six yards apiece, was bumped off a punt catch by his own teammates and otherwise avoided by Packers’ punter Tim Masthay. 
Writing for the 49ers’ official website, Taylor Price said Hayne - coming off a terrific 37-yard return that led to a touchdown the previous game - was treated like an NFL veteran by the Packers. 
“Jarryd Hayne appears to have settled into his role as the starting punt returner for the San Francisco 49ers,” Price wrote. 
“In Sunday’s 17-3 loss to the Green Bay Packers, the 27-year-old rookie was treated like a veteran returner, too. Packers punter Tim Masthay attempted six punts on the day. Three of those balls were placed out of bounds away from Hayne.” 
Price continued: “Hayne, however, did not get much of an opportunity to spark San Francisco’s offense like he did a week before with a 37-yard return against the Arizona Cardinals. Other Stories
